Dionysius of Halicarnassus Literary Composition [the Cretic]: There remains one type of three-syllable rhythm which consists of two longs and a short, and makes three kinds of metre. lf it has the short in the middle and the longs at either end it is called a cretio, and it is not an ignoble metre. This is an example of it:

And they hastened forward with their floating chariots bronze-enipointed.5
